The definition `cfc_toLinearFunctional` defines a continuous linear functional on `C((spectrum ℂ a), ℂ)`. For a function `f` on the spectrum, it maps `f` to the inner product `⟨x, (f(a)) y⟩_ℂ`. This is constructed by composing `toLinearFunctional x y` (which is a linear functional on operators) with `cfcCLM ha` (which maps `f` to an operator `f(a)`).

